      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a PhD student in the School of Computing at the University of Utah in the robotics track of the &lt;a href=&#34;http://robotics.coe.utah.edu/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Utah Robotics Center&lt;/a&gt;. I work in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://robot-learning.cs.utah.edu/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Utah Learning Lab for Manipulation Autonomy&lt;/a&gt; (LL4MA) and am advised by &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cs.utah.edu/~thermans/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Dr. Tucker Hermans&lt;/a&gt;. My research interests include learning manipulation tasks from human demonstration and multisensory interactive perception. I am passionate about open source software development for robotics, particularly for the ROS framework.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
